Yeah NPC's are on spawn timers, for X amount of minutes after PC ganks them.  Sorry bud, hate to do this to ya.  If mob spawns 6 minutes after pc ganks it, then max it should take for epic to DS would be 6 minutes with your logic.  Yes PC's cast pets at completely random times, same as we kill NPC's at completely random times, which ultimately makes NPC's spawn at completely random times (few exceptions).  <br>
<br>
If I randomly gank NCP mage, then NPC mage will respawn and instantly start it's spawn routine.  This same routine should be followed by our pets.  Since it doesn't matter when I kill the npc it will respawn on it's spawn timer (6-14 minutes for most spawns), and has a spawn buff routine that it follows.  <br>
<br>
Sorry man, I hate to do that on your first post, your logic was on for the most part.  You just failed to see the randomness of when we PC's kill the NPC's.<br>
